<a href="/updates?edit=nm0000450/details&ref_=nm_pdt_edt" > Edit
</a>        </span>
    <h2>Personal Details</h2>
        <div id="details-other-works" class="see-more inline canwrap">
                <h4 class="inline">Other Works:</h4>
                	Stage credits include: 
Jane Anderson's "Defying Gavity" at the American Palace Theatre; "The Merchant Of Venice" directed by Peter Sellers; and the Williamstown Theatre Productions of "Henry V" and "Mother Courage"; the off- Broadway production of "Shopping And Fucking" by Mark Ravenhill; and the 2000 Broadway production of "True West".                    <span class="see-more inline">
                        <a href="/name/nm0000450/otherworks?ref_=nm_pdt_wrk_sm" >See more</a> 
                    </span>
                    &raquo;
        </div>
    
    
            <hr/>
        <div id="details-akas" class="see-more inline canwrap">
            <h4 class="inline">Alternate Names:</h4>
            Philip S. Hoffman <span>|</span> Philip Hoffman <span>|</span> Phillip Seymour Hoffman <span>|</span> Phil Hoffman
        </div>
    
            <hr/>
        <div id="details-height" class="see-more inline canwrap">
            <h4 class="inline">Height:</h4>
5'&nbsp;9½"&nbsp;(1.77&nbsp;m)        </div>
            </div> 
            <div class="article">
        <span class="rightcornerlink">
<a href="/updates?edit=nm0000450/fun-facts&ref_=nm_dyk_edt" > Edit
</a>        </span>
    <h2>Did You Know?</h2>
        <div id="dyk-personal-quote" class="see-more inline canwrap">
                <h4 class="inline">Personal Quote:</h4>
"Other people disagree with me, but Scent of a Woman really was my breakthrough. I was working in the prepared foods section of a deli when I was cast in that movie, and I've never had a non-acting job since. That's amazing".                    <span class="see-more inline">
                        <a href="/name/nm0000450/bio?ref_=nm_dyk_qt_sm#quotes" >See more</a> 
                    </span>
                    &raquo;
        </div>
            <hr/>
        <div id="dyk-trivia" class="see-more inline canwrap">
                <h4 class="inline">Trivia:</h4>
In 2002, he appeared in <a href="/title/tt0307901/?ref_=nm_dyk_trv1">25th Hour</a> (2002), opposite <a href="/name/nm0001570/?ref_=nm_dyk_trv2">Edward Norton</a> and <a href="/name/nm0004051/?ref_=nm_dyk_trv3">Brian Cox</a>; and in <a href="/title/tt0272338/?ref_=nm_dyk_trv4">Punch-Drunk Love</a> (2002), opposite <a href="/name/nm0001833/?ref_=nm_dyk_trv5">Emily Watson</a>. That same year, he appeared with both Norton and Watson in <a href="/title/tt0289765/?ref_=nm_dyk_trv6">Red Dragon</a> (2002), which was a remake of <a href="/title/tt0091474/?ref_=nm_dyk_trv7">Manhunter</a> (1986), in which Cox had appeared.                    <span class="see-more inline">
                        <a href="/name/nm0000450/bio?ref_=nm_dyk_trv_sm#trivia" >See more</a>
                    </span>
                    &raquo;
        </div>
    
            <hr/>
        <div id="dyk-trademark" class="see-more inline canwrap">

                <h4 class="inline">Trademark:</h4>
His characters often ran through a wide range of emotions                    <span class="see-more inline">
                        <a href="/name/nm0000450/bio?ref_=nm_dyk_tm_sm#trademark" >See more</a>
                    </span>
                    &raquo;
        </div>
    
            <hr/>
        <div id="dyk-nickname" class="see-more inline canwrap">
            <h4 class="inline">Nickname:</h4>
            Phil
        </div>
            <hr/>
        <div id="dyk-star-sign" class="see-more inline canwrap">
            <h4 class="inline">Star Sign:</h4>
            <a href="/starsign/leo?ref_=nm_dyk_sign" >Leo</a>
        </div>
            </div> 
    </div>
